<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900529-0156</DOCNO><DOCID>900529-0156.</DOCID><HL>   NTT's Foreign Purchases Rise</HL><DATE>05/29/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   J.NTT</CO><IN>MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)</IN><LP>   TOKYO -- Nippon Telegraph andamp; Telephone Corp. said itsprocurement from foreign suppliers rose 22% in fiscal 1990 to50.4 billion yen ($334 million), exceeding the company'sconstruction investment.   In the year ended March 31, the telecommunications companysubstantially raised overseas purchases of such items asdigital equipment, optical fiber cables, digital transmissionand information processing equipment.</LP><TEXT>   Foreign procurement of pocket pagers and mobile telephoneequipment rose.   The U.S. accounted for 90% of the total increasedprocurement.</TEXT></DOC>